flavor.CS2_039: Windfury is like Earthfury and Firefury, but more light and airy.
flavor.EX1_587: Is there anything worse than a Windspeaker with halitosis?
flavor.CS2_124: Orcish raiders ride wolves because they are well adapted to harsh environments, and because they are soft and cuddly.
flavor.GVG_077: The Dark Animus is evil and mysterious and huge and unable to write sentences that utilize proper grammar.
flavor.GVG_085: The inventor of the Annoy-o-Tron was immediately expelled from Tinkerschool, Tinkertown, and was eventually exiled from the Eastern Kingdoms altogether.
flavor.GVG_030: It's adorable! AND OH MY GOODNESS WHY IS IT EATING MY FACE
flavor.GVG_069: They don't make 'em like they used to! (Because of explosions, mostly.)
flavor.GVG_091: There was some hard talk between gnome magi and engineers about inventing this mech.
flavor.GVG_119: PREPARE PARTY SERVOS FOR IMMEDIATE DEPLOYMENT.
flavor.GVG_063: Spoiler alert: Bolvar gets melted and then sits on an ice throne and everyone forgets about him.
flavor.GVG_099: He lobbies Orgrimmar daily on behalf of bombs.
flavor.GVG_050: Only goblins would think this was a good idea. Even they are starting to have their doubts.
flavor.GVG_068: He's burly because he does CrossFit.
flavor.GVG_121: He and Mountain Giant don't get along.
flavor.GVG_082: Clockwork gnomes are always asking what time it is.
flavor.GVG_062: Guardians used to be built out of Adamantium, but production got moved to Gadgetzan and Cobalt was cheap.
flavor.GVG_073: "Cobra Shot" hurts way, way, way more than "Cobra Cuddle."
flavor.GVG_059: So you ripped this out of a machine, carved some runes on it, stuck it on a handle, and now it's a weapon of great divine power? Seems legit.
flavor.GVG_013: After a while, you don't see the cogs and sprockets. All you see is a robot, a spider tank, a deathray...
flavor.GVG_024: For tightening cogs and smashin' troggs!
flavor.GVG_052: Using this card on your enemies is one of the best things in life, according to some barbarians.
flavor.GVG_041: Don't worry; we fired the person who named this card.
flavor.GVG_015: If you're looking to make an "Emo" deck, this card is perfect!
flavor.GVG_019: Virtually every member of the pro demon lobby is a warlock. Weird.
flavor.GVG_080: The Druids of the Fang live in the Wailing Caverns. They wear cool snake shirts and tell snake jokes and say "bro" a lot.
flavor.GVG_066: He just closes his eyes and goes for it. Raarararrrarar!
flavor.GVG_005: Medivh's echo haunts Karazhan, eternally cheating at chess and Hearthstone.
flavor.GVG_076: How is this supposed to work? Your enemies think, "Hey! Cute sheep!" and run over to cuddle it?
flavor.GVG_026: The hardest part about doing a "Feign Death" convincingly is learning how to make the right smell. It takes a lot of commitment.
flavor.GVG_020: The box says, "New and improved, with 200% more fel!"
flavor.GVG_007: Mimiron likes to take the Flame Leviathan out on some sweet joyrides.
flavor.GVG_001: Calling something a flamecannon really doesn't do much to distinguish it from other goblin devices.
flavor.GVG_100: "Evil Eye Watcher of Doom" was the original name, but marketing felt it was a bit too aggressive.
flavor.GVG_084: To operate, this contraption needs a hula doll on the dashboard. Otherwise it's just a “falling machine.”
flavor.GVG_113: Foe reaping is really not so different from harvest reaping, at the end of the day.
flavor.GVG_079: There is a factory in Tanaris for crafting force-tanks, but it only ever made two, because of cost overruns.
flavor.GVG_049: The Sen'jin High football team is The Gahz'rillas.
flavor.GVG_117: Gazlowe was voted "Most Likely to Explode" in high school.
flavor.GVG_081:
"Shhh, I think I hear something."
"Ah, it's probably nothing." - Every Henchman
flavor.GVG_043: For the times when a regular bazooka just isn't enough.
flavor.GVG_098: The gnomes are valiant and ready to return to their irradiated, poorly ventilated homeland!
flavor.GVG_092: He's legitimately surprised every time he turns himself into a chicken.
flavor.GVG_023: This guy is excellent at adjusting your haircut and/or height.
flavor.GVG_004: If you can't find a bomb to throw, just pick up any goblin invention and throw that.
flavor.GVG_095: He’s not such a binge exploder anymore. These days, he only explodes socially.
flavor.GVG_032: Likes: Hiking and the great outdoors. Dislikes: Goblin shredders and sandals. (Can’t find any that fit!).
flavor.GVG_120: It's hard to make a living as a hunter in a world where beasts instantly reappear minutes after you kill them.
flavor.GVG_104: Hobgoblins are meeting next week to discuss union benefits.  First on the list: dental plan.
flavor.GVG_089: "LUMOS!" is not what they yell. What do you think this is, Hogwarts?
flavor.GVG_045: The shrapnel is waaaaay worse than the explosion.
flavor.GVG_056: The Iron Juggernaut guards Orgrimmar and has just earned the "Employee of the Month" award!
flavor.GVG_027:
Mechs like learning from him because he really speaks their language.
0110100001101001
flavor.GVG_094: This robot is a lean, mean, butlerin' machine.
flavor.GVG_106: One bot's junk is another bot's AWESOME UPGRADE!
flavor.GVG_074: They pretend to be wise and enlightened, but they mostly just hate to be left out of a secret.
flavor.GVG_046: He never sleeps.  Not even in the mighty jungle.
flavor.GVG_012: "Light it up!" - Command given to both Lightwardens and Goblins holding Flamecannons.
flavor.GVG_008: This is what happens when you allow goblins to be priests.
flavor.GVG_097: Warlocks have the town exorcist on speed dial in case they unleash the wrong demon.
flavor.GVG_071: The message, "If found, please return to Mulgore," is tattooed on his rear.
flavor.GVG_021: Mal'Ganis doesn't like being betrayed, so if you discard him, watch out.
flavor.GVG_035: When Malorne isn't mauling hordes of demons, he enjoys attending parties, though he prefers to go stag.
flavor.GVG_034: Crushes buildings with his BEAR hands.
flavor.GVG_078: The yetis of Chillwind Point are a source of both inspiration and savage beatings.
flavor.GVG_006: Mechs that summon mechs? What's next? Donuts that summon donuts? Mmmmm.
flavor.GVG_116: He was obsessed with explosives until he discovered knitting. Now he yells, “SWEATERS! MORE SWEATERS!”
flavor.GVG_048: Don't leave them out in the rain. In Un'Goro Crater there is a whole colony of rust-tooth leapers.
flavor.GVG_103: This card is the real thing.
flavor.GVG_111: Do not push the big red button!
flavor.GVG_109: He is sometimes found hiding in the treasure chest in the Gurubashi Arena.
flavor.GVG_018: Her sister is the Mistress of Pane who sells windows and shower doors.
flavor.GVG_112: Mogor helped reopen the Dark Portal once. You know you're in trouble when you have to rely on an ogre.
flavor.GVG_061: "I'm bringing the guacamole!" – One of the most successful (yet rare) Silver Hand rallying cries
flavor.GVG_042: Neptulon is "The Tidehunter". He’s one of the four elemental lords. And he and Ragnaros get together and make really amazing saunas.
flavor.GVG_065: Ogres have really terrible short-term chocolate.
flavor.GVG_088: He didn't have the grades to get into ninja school, but his dad pulled some strings.
flavor.GVG_054: Simple, misguided, and incredibly dangerous. You know, like most things ogre.
flavor.GVG_025: When pirates say there is no "Eye" in "team," they are very literal about it.
flavor.GVG_096: Once upon a time, only goblins piloted shredders. These days, everyone from Doomsayer to Lorewalker Cho seems to ride one.
flavor.GVG_105: The pinnacle of goblin engineering. Includes an espresso machine and foot massager.
flavor.GVG_036: People assume that shamans control the elements, but really, they have to ask them stuff and the elements are like, "Yeah ok, sure."
flavor.GVG_064: He pays homage to Morgl, the great murloc oracle! (Who doesn't??)
flavor.GVG_060: His specialty? Dividing things into four pieces.
flavor.GVG_108: For when you didn’t combobulate quite right the first time around.
flavor.GVG_031: Druidic recycling involves putting plastics in one bin and enemy minions in another bin.
flavor.GVG_047: Rogues can't stand it. They know you planned it! They are going to set you straight!
flavor.GVG_070: He's recently recovered from being a "scurvy dog."
flavor.GVG_101: The Scarlet Crusade is doing market research to find out if the "Mauve Crusade" would be better received.
flavor.GVG_055: If it breaks, just kick it a couple of times while yelling "Durn thing!"
flavor.GVG_057: The walrus of Light restores EIGHT Health.
flavor.GVG_009: Shadowbomber does her job, but she's kind of phoning it in at this point.
flavor.GVG_072: Punching is its primary function. Also, its secondary function.
flavor.GVG_058: He chooses to believe what he is programmed to believe!
flavor.GVG_053: She has three shieldbearers in her party to supply her with back ups when she gets low on durability.
flavor.GVG_075: If you hear someone yell, "Cannonball!" you're about to get wet. Or crushed.
flavor.GVG_011: After the debacle of the Gnomish World Enlarger, gnomes are wary of size-changing inventions.
flavor.GVG_040: The elements respond to anyone who calls them for a worthy cause, even if you call them by yelling, "MRGHRGLGLGL!"
flavor.GVG_114: When Sneed was defeated in the Deadmines, his shredder was sold at auction to an anonymous buyer. (Probably Hogger.)
flavor.GVG_002: Do the slow chant when he waddles by: "Chug! Chug! Chug!"
flavor.GVG_123: The inventor of the goblin shredder is involved in several patent disputes with the inventor of the soot spewer.
flavor.GVG_044: "What if we put guns on it?" -Fizzblitz, staring at the spider-transportation-machine
flavor.GVG_087: Goblins seldom have the patience for sniping. Most prefer lobbing explosives.
flavor.GVG_067: The only thing worse than smelling troggs is listening to their poetry.
flavor.GVG_093: The engineering equivalent of a "Kick Me" sticker.
flavor.GVG_022: "Get ready to strike oil!" - Super-cheesy battle cry
flavor.GVG_102: Won't you take me to... Tinkertown?
flavor.GVG_028: Gallywix believes in supply and demand. He supplies the beatings and demands you pay up!
flavor.GVG_118: He keeps earthinating the countryside despite attempts to stop him.
flavor.GVG_003: The denizens of Azeroth have no idea how much work goes into stabilizing portals.  We spend like 30% of GDP on portal upkeep.
flavor.GVG_083: It's the same as the previous generation but they slapped the word "upgraded" on it to sell it for double.
flavor.GVG_010: Velen wrote a "Lovely Card" for Tyrande with a picture of the Deeprun Tram that said "I Choo-Choo-Choose you!"
flavor.GVG_039: You can usually find these at the totemist's market on Saturdays.
flavor.GVG_014: Vol'jin is a shadow hunter, which is like a shadow priest except more voodoo.
flavor.GVG_051: Mass production of warbots was halted when it was discovered that they were accidentally being produced at "sample size."
flavor.GVG_122: Bane of spellcasters and spelling bees everywhere.
flavor.GVG_037: If you pay a little extra, you can get it in "candy-apple red."
